{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "BasicShapes",
  "description": "Trigger-cycled 2D SDF shapes — Square / Diamond / Octagon, anti-aliased with a per-pixel fwidth approximation. Decomposed onto three `node.basic_shape` instances (one per shape) muxed at output via `node.mux_texture`; the shape selection is visible as a graph wiring instead of a sealed compiled-enum.\n\nCycling math is in JSON: `clip_trigger_index` cycles through variants (3 in Solid / Wireframe, 6 in Mixed) with `node.math` deriving `shape_idx = variant % 3`, `rot_step = floor(tc / modulus) % 8`, and `is_wireframe = floor(variant / 3)` for the Mixed mode's interleaved fill flip. The 8 signed rotation snap angles live as inline `in_N` params on a `mux_scalar` table (`feedback_inline_mux_option_table_params`).\n\nRotation easing is `node.trigger_ease_to(window_beats=0.25)`: on each new trigger edge it samples the current visible rotation as `prev`, locks the new target as `curr`, and eases between them along a cubic ease-out over the next quarter beat. Reusable atom; any snap-on-clip-trigger-and-glide-over-a-tempo-locked-window control surface uses the same shape.\n\nThe `Clip Trigger` toggle gates the cycling via three output muxes (shape_idx, is_wireframe, target_angle). When OFF: shape freezes at variant 0 (Square / Wireframe-Square depending on fill mode) and rotation snaps to 0. When ON: the cycle drives shape + rotation snap from `trigger_count`. Note: the eased rotation runs unconditionally and is suppressed at the output gate, so re-enabling clip_trigger eases into the new variant over the quarter-beat window instead of snapping — small accepted parity delta vs the legacy reset-on-disable behaviour.\n\nFuture shape additions: extend `node.basic_shape`'s WGSL `switch` + bump the enum table, then drop a new `basic_shape` instance into this graph's mux (with shape_idx cycle widened to match). Genuinely novel SDFs that don't fit a `case` (Heart, Star, parametric ones) ship as sibling atoms and join the same mux.",
